        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 18:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where the order of the two sayings is inverted. Assuming the words to have been repeated where we find them here, the “little ones” must mean the disciples of Christ who are, in both senses of the word “offended” by the worldliness of those who profess to be religious. They are made to stumble by the temptation to follow the bad example, or their faith in the reality of godliness is shaken by seeing that the form exists without the power.",
        "children": []
