  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "It were better (λυσιτελεῖ)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Only here in New Testament. The verb means to pay what is due, and is equivalent to our phrase, it pays.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Millstone",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Compare Matthew 18:6. The correct reading here is λίθος μυλικός, a millstone; not a great millstone as Matthew",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Compare ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 18:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The correct reading here is λίθος μυλικός, a millstone; not a great millstone as Matthew",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Thrown (ἔῤῥιπται)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hurled: with an underlying sense of violence, called out by so great an outrage.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]